<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Representation of a single sample record.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><Highlight kind="comment">/// A sample record is represented by a positive integer value, which</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><Highlight kind="comment">/// indicates how frequently was the associated line location executed.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Additionally, if the associated location contains a function call,</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00322" /><CodeLine lineNumber="322"><Highlight kind="comment">/// direct calls, this will be the exact function being invoked. For</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00323" /><CodeLine lineNumber="323"><Highlight kind="comment">/// indirect calls (function pointers, virtual table dispatch), this</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00324" /><CodeLine lineNumber="324"><Highlight kind="comment">/// will be a list of one or more functions.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprof/samplerecord"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">class </Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sampleprof/samplerecord/#a9e45fc6fb7b892f8d86be28794da2dbd">SampleRecord</a> &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00513" /><CodeLine lineNumber="513"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Sample context for FunctionSamples. It consists of the calling context,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00514" /><CodeLine lineNumber="514"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// the function name and context state. Internally sample context is represented</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00515" /><CodeLine lineNumber="515"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// using ArrayRef, which is also the input for constructing a &#96;SampleContext&#96;.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00516" /><CodeLine lineNumber="516"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// It can accept and represent both full context string as well as context-less</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00517" /><CodeLine lineNumber="517"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// function name.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00518" /><CodeLine lineNumber="518"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For a CS profile, a full context vector can look like:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00519" /><CodeLine lineNumber="519"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    &#96;main:3 &#95;Z5funcAi:1 &#95;Z8funcLeafi&#96;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00520" /><CodeLine lineNumber="520"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For a base CS profile without calling context, the context vector should only</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00521" /><CodeLine lineNumber="521"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// contain the leaf frame name.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00522" /><CodeLine lineNumber="522"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For a non-CS profile, the context vector should be empty.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
